A collection of utility code, mainly for behavioral control and analysis or neural data acquisition and analysis.

Mark Histed
mhisted@gmail.com

----------------

Some routines of interest:

import mathMH
mathMH.chop()   # rounds to a specified number of sig digits
mathMH.smooth() # smoothing using filtering, e.g. with a Hamming window

----------------

Install notes:

    # for developing (working directly in source dir):
    #   this adds the source dir path to site-packages/easy-install.pth
    sudo python setup.py develop  

    # alternate: copies these files to site-packages
    sudo python setup.py install

